medical_history.chief_complaint: Unresponsiveness after feeding, leading to cardiac arrest.
medical_history.history_of_present_illness: The symptoms began 30 hours after birth when the infant became unresponsive 2 hours after the last feeding. There were initial grunting episodes noted on the first day of life, which resolved spontaneously. Resuscitation efforts lasted for 2 hours before being discontinued.
medical_history.past_medical_history: The infant was born following an uncomplicated pregnancy.
